tation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes de Peynel was born about 1115, her father, Fulk Paganell, was 66 and her mother, Dame Beatrix de Picquigny, was 57. She married Robert de BRUCE in 1135, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1115–":"umbes 1115–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1135–1190":"1135–1190","1050–1130":"1050–1130","1059–1130":"1059–1130","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","1190":"1190","1115":"1115","1059":"1059","1135":"1135","ABT 1135":"umbes 1135","about 1115":"umbes 1115","1130":"1130","1050":"1050","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1115–":"noin 1115–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1135–1190":"1135–1190","1050–1130":"1050–1130","1059–1130":"1059–1130","1115–Female":"1115–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1115":"1115","1059":"1059","1135":"1135","ABT 1135":"noin 1135","about 1115":"noin 1115","1130":"1130","1050":"1050","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1115–":"environ 1115–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1135–1190":"1135–1190","1050–1130":"1050–1130","1059–1130":"1059–1130","1115–Female":"1115–Décédée","1190":"1190","1115":"1115","1059":"1059","1135":"1135","ABT 1135":"environ 1135","about 1115":"environ 1115","1130":"1130","1050":"1050","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Agnes de Peynel est née environ 1115, son père, Fulk Paganell, avait 66 ans et sa mère, Dame Beatrix de Picquigny, avait 57 ans. Elle a épousé Robert de BRUCE en 1135, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1115–":"um 